02/11/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Deputy Interior Minister Boyko Kotsev said Friday (31 October) the country was prepared to guard the EU's outer border. 
He pointed to achievements in the field of security, including the demilitarisation of the Border Police National Service and strengthened monitoring and control of borders along the Danube and the Black Sea. 
That same day, Bulgaria launched a project to expand and upgrade the Gyueshevo border checkpoint with Macedonia. 
(BTA, BNT, BNR, AFP - 02/11/03; Trud - 01/11/03; BTA, BNT, BNR - 31/10/03)
